# Dhall config topology — ALL Dhall is generated or locally authored, and NONE
# is version-controlled (binary-owned / per-host / secret-bearing LOCAL config).
#   * prodbox-config.dhall (retired, Sprint 1.42) / test-secrets.dhall carry
#     secrets. Sprint 1.43: test-secrets.dhall is the ONLY durable-secret fixture
#     file (the vault unlock password, the durable elevated AWS credential, and
#     the ZeroSSL ACME EAB key) — there is no non-secret test-config.dhall.
#   * prodbox.dhall is the Tier-0 binary-context config (config_doctrine §0) and
#     the SOLE source of the sealed-Vault bootstrap floor (projected off its
#     `context`); it is binary-owned + per-host, written by the binary (writeTier0
#     / ensureBasicsFloor), never committed.
#   * docker/default-prodbox.dhall is the in-cluster container's baked-in default
#     Tier-0 config. It is REGENERATED into the build context from the Haskell
#     source of truth immediately before every `docker build` (see
#     ensureDaemonContainerDefaultDhall), so it is generated, not committed.
prodbox-config.dhall
prodbox-config.json
test-secrets.dhall
prodbox.dhall
docker/default-prodbox.dhall

# Sprint 7.17 / 1.43: the Dhall schema files are GENERATED from the Haskell
# source of truth (`prodbox config schema`), not hand-maintained. They are
# materialized on disk so imports/test fixtures resolve, but are no longer
# version-controlled.
prodbox-config-types.dhall
test-secrets-types.dhall

